		<header>
			
			<h1>Debate intensifies on Kenyan maize imports</h1>

			
			<h4>
												03 October 2014
										</h4>

					</header>


		
		
					<p>According to FAO, cereal production in Eastern Africa is expected to have increased by 0.9% between 2012 and 2014, with a projected annual increase of 4.15% in 2014. However, two of the major cereal producing countries, Kenya and Uganda, will see production continuing to decrease in 2014, taking the cumulative fall over the 2012–14 period to 15.6% and 14.3% respectively. Somalia, Rwanda and Burundi are also forecast to face below-average levels of cereal production. Even in countries where production is growing, some regions will face shortfalls.</p><p><b>Eastern African cereal production, including rice (million tonnes)</b></p><table class="renderedtable" border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0">
<tr>
<td width="123" valign="top">  &nbsp;
